@startuml PFE-Flux-E2E-Securise

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #2196F3
  ActorBorderColor #555555
  LifeLineBorderColor #999999
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FAFAFA
  ParticipantBorderColor #555555
}

title Flux de Communication E2E Sécurisé — PFE IoT Security TT

actor "IoT Device\n(Capteur)" as DEVICE
participant "MikroTik\n(Switch L3)" as SW
participant "pfSense\n(Firewall)" as FW
participant "MQTT Broker\n(Mosquitto)" as BROKER
participant "HashiCorp\nVault (PKI)" as VAULT
participant "Wazuh\n(SIEM)" as WAZUH
participant "Suricata\n(IDS)" as SURICATA
participant "ML Engine\n(Anomaly Det.)" as ML

== Phase 1 : Provisionnement du certificat ==

DEVICE -> VAULT : [mTLS] Demande certificat client\n(CSR)
VAULT -> VAULT : Validation identité device\nGénération certificat signé
VAULT --> DEVICE : Certificat X.509 + CA chain
note right of VAULT : PKI Engine\nTTL = 24h\nRotation automatique

== Phase 2 : Connexion sécurisée au Broker ==

DEVICE -> SW : Paquet TCP SYN (port 8883)
SW -> FW : Routage VLAN 10 → VLAN 20
FW -> FW : Vérification règles ACL\n(IoT → DMZ autorisé)
FW -> BROKER : Forward TCP SYN
BROKER -> DEVICE : TLS 1.3 Handshake\n(Server Hello + Certificate)
DEVICE -> BROKER : Client Certificate\n(mTLS authentication)
BROKER -> VAULT : Vérification CRL/OCSP
VAULT --> BROKER : Certificat valide ✅

note over DEVICE, BROKER : Canal chiffré établi\nTLS 1.3 — AES-256-GCM\nmTLS bidirectionnel

== Phase 3 : Publication des données IoT ==

DEVICE -> BROKER : [TLS] MQTT CONNECT\n(ClientID + credentials)
BROKER --> DEVICE : MQTT CONNACK (RC=0)
DEVICE -> BROKER : [TLS] MQTT PUBLISH\nTopic: iot/sensors/temp/01\nPayload: {"temp": 23.5, "ts": "..."}
BROKER --> DEVICE : MQTT PUBACK

== Phase 4 : Surveillance et détection ==

BROKER -> WAZUH : Logs MQTT (connexion + publish)
SW -> SURICATA : Port mirroring — copie du trafic
SURICATA -> SURICATA : Analyse règles IDS\nDétection anomalies réseau
SURICATA -> WAZUH : Alerte IDS (si détection)
WAZUH -> ML : Export logs pour analyse ML
ML -> ML : IsolationForest\nDétection comportements anormaux
ML --> WAZUH : Score d'anomalie + classification

== Phase 5 : Rotation des clés ==

VAULT -> DEVICE : Notification renouvellement\n(TTL expirant)
DEVICE -> VAULT : [mTLS] Renouvellement certificat
VAULT --> DEVICE : Nouveau certificat X.509

@enduml